 [[Painting 3]]
 [[Painting 4]]


:: Approach the paintings {"position":"675,650","size":"100,100"}






At the end of the <span style="color:#ff4d4d; text-shadow: 0 0 6px #ff0000;">Red Hall</span> the paths diverge. Each character is called in a different way toward their own destiny in the cave.
<video class="video-bg" autoplay loop muted playsinline>
  <source src="https://ChenQingHa.github.io/grotta-vr-media/四个角色.mp4" type="video/mp4">
</video>
A question rises — not spoken, but felt:


Who are you in this place?




[[Shaman]]
[[Warrior]]
[[Devotee I]]
[[Devotee II]]
[[Dancer]]


:: Ask shaman for healing {"position":"475,1350","size":"100,100"}
<div class="handprint2">
<p class="whisper">it's so silent......</p>
<div class="poetic">
<span class="glow">You step inside.</span>


<span class="whisper">Not as a guardian.</span>

<span class="whisper">Not this time.</span>


<span class="glow">The wound burns.</span>


Each step is slower than the last.

The cave no longer feels like something to defend.

<span class="whisper">It feels… distant.</span>


The fire behind you fades.

Another light appears ahead —
lower,
quieter.


You reach a chamber.


<span class="glow-breath">A figure is already there.</span>


Still.

Waiting.


<span class="glow">The shaman.</span>


They do not ask.

They do not question.

<span class="whisper">They see.</span>


You sit.

Or perhaps you collapse.


The shaman moves.


Hands over dried plants,
crushing them slowly,
releasing a sharp, bitter scent.


Powder mixes with moisture.

Dark paste.


Their hands approach your wound.

<span class="glow">Firm.</span>

<span class="glow">Precise.</span>


<span class="glow">Pain.</span>


<span class="glow-breath">Then warmth.</span>


The cave grows softer.


The walls begin to shift.

Only slightly.


A line moves.

A deer runs —
but slower than before.

A figure turns.


<span class="whisper">Not a vision.</span>

<span class="whisper">Not fully.</span>


Something between body and image.


Your breathing steadies.

The pain loosens its grip.


The shaman says nothing.

But their gestures are enough.


<span class="glow">Healing is not separate from meaning.</span>


What touches the body
touches something else.


The movement fades.


The walls return.


The cave is still.


You remain.


<span class="glow-strong glow-breath">Changed.</span>

</div>

[[Continue]]

</div>


