</video>



You have a fight with them and get hurt.




[[Ask shaman for healing]] 


:: Enter the experience {"position":"650,25","size":"100,100"}



You open your eyes.

You are no longer in the room.

The sea stretches behind you.
The sky burns with a deep orange light.

<video class="video-bg" autoplay loop muted playsinline>
  <source src="https://ChenQingHa.github.io/grotta-vr-media/夕阳洞.mp4" type="video/mp4">
</video>

The cave stands before you.

Waiting.

[[Approach the cave]]


:: Enter the movement {"position":"1100,1025","size":"100,100"}
<video class="video-bg" autoplay loop muted playsinline>
  <source src="https://ChenQingHa.github.io/grotta-vr-media/幻视.mp4" type="video/mp4">
</video>
<video class="video-bg" autoplay loop muted playsinline>
  <source src="https://ChenQingHa.github.io/grotta-vr-media/巫术3.mp4" type="video/mp4">
</video>
<p class="whisper">You become a synchrony surrender........</p>
<div class="poetic">
The rhythm continues.


It does not stop when you move.


<span class="glow">It moves with you.</span>


The corridor narrows.

The sound becomes clearer.


Layered now —
steps,
breath,
something like a voice.


<span class="glow-breath">The shaman appears.</span>


They do not react to your presence.

They do not question it.


They extend their hand.


A branch.

Dry.

Light.


<span class="glow">You take it.</span>


<span class="glow-strong glow-breath">"Your body will open the way."</span>


The words do not echo.

They settle.


The shaman turns.

You follow.


<span class="whisper">Not by decision.</span>


<span class="glow">By rhythm.</span>


Step.

Step.

Step.


The walls begin to blur
when you fall out of time.


Then sharpen again
when you return.


You do not lead.

You do not resist.


<span class="glow-strong glow-breath">You align.</span>

</div>

[[Experience the dance]]

</div>


:: Enter the rite {"position":"550,1475","size":"100,100"}
<p class="whisper">quite world....</p>
<div class="handprint2">
<div class="poetic">

<span class="glow">You enter the Sanctuary.</span>


The space is still.

Larger than before,
but quieter.


The walls surround you.

Figures remain where they were.

Unmoving.

Silent.


<span class="whisper">Except one.</span>


<span class="glow-breath">The one you chose.</span>


At first,
nothing happens.


Then —


<span class="glow">a shift.</span>


Not a step.

Not a gesture.


A change in presence.


The line softens.

<span class="glow-breath">The form breathes.</span>


The figure moves.


Slowly.


<span class="whisper">Not as a body moves.</span>

As a drawing moves —
along its own lines,
within its own limits.


You do not hear words.


You do not need to.


<span class="glow">The movement is enough.</span>


A hand raised.

A turn of the head.

A repetition of a gesture
you have seen before.


Something is being said.


<span class="whisper">Not clearly.</span>

<span class="whisper">Not completely.</span>


But directly.


<span class="glow-strong glow-breath">To you.</span>


You understand
without knowing how.


<span class="glow">Memory is not behind you.</span>

<span class="glow-strong glow-breath">It is here.</span>


The movement slows.


The figure returns.


Line by line,
still again.


The wall holds it.


As it always has.


Silence.


You remain.


The shaman is beside you.


They do not speak.


They point.


A place on the wall.


Empty.


<span class="glow-strong glow-breath">Waiting.</span>

</div>

[[Reflect on the whole journey]]

[[Return to the entrance->Approach the paintings]]
</div>



:: Experience the dance {"position":"1175,1175","size":"100,100"}
<video class="video-bg" autoplay loop muted playsinline>
  <source src="https://ChenQingHa.github.io/grotta-vr-media/幻视.mp4" type="video/mp4">
</video>
<p class="whisper">Moment of loss of self....</p>\
<video class="video-bg" autoplay loop muted playsinline>
  <source src="https://ChenQingHa.github.io/grotta-vr-media/巫术1.mp4" type="video/mp4">
</video>
<div class="poetic">

The rhythm does not stop.


<span class="glow">It grows.</span>


Faster.

Closer.

<span class="glow-breath">Inside you.</span>


Your steps are no longer yours.

They continue
even when you do not decide.


<span class="glow">The walls respond.</span>


Figures multiply.

Six become many.

Movement overlaps movement.


There is no centre anymore.

<span class="glow-breath">Only repetition.</span>


You turn.

<span class="whisper">Or something turns you.</span>


The lines on the wall begin to extend.

Toward you.

Around you.


They do not stay on the surface.


<span class="glow">They enter.</span>


Your arms repeat their shape.

Your body follows their curve.


You are no longer matching the rhythm.

<span class="glow-strong glow-breath">You are inside it.</span>


The figures do not surround you.


<span class="glow">They include you.</span>


For a moment —


<span class="glow-strong glow-breath">you are one of them.</span>


A line.

A movement.

A trace without weight.


No beginning.

No end.


—


<span class="whisper">Silence.</span>


Immediate.


Absolute.


The movement breaks.


You are standing.


The Sanctuary.


Still.


Empty.


The walls hold their images again.


<span class="whisper">As if nothing moved.</span>


<span class="whisper">As if nothing happened.</span>


But something remains.


A space.


A place where a figure was.


<span class="glow-strong glow-breath">Your place.</span>


Waiting.

</div>

[[Reflect on the whole journey]]

[[Return to the entrance->Approach the paintings]]
</div>



:: Go to Sanctuary for rituals {"position":"75,1000","size":"100,100"}
<video class="video-bg" autoplay loop muted playsinline>
  <source src="https://ChenQingHa.github.io/grotta-vr-media/山洞2.mp4" type="video/mp4">
</video>
<p class="whisper">The space opens —
wider than expected,
deeper than it should be.
<video class="video-bg" autoplay loop muted playsinline>
  <source src="https://ChenQingHa.github.io/grotta-vr-media/幻视.mp4" type="video/mp4">
</video>
The air is still.</p>
<div class="poetic">
You enter the <span style="color:#fff; text-shadow: 0 0 8px #ffcc66;">Sanctuary</span>.

<span class="glow-breath">The cave is waiting.</span>


You do not hesitate.


<span class="glow">The ritual begins.</span>


You close your eyes.


<span class="whisper">Darkness.</span>


Then —


<span class="glow-strong glow-breath">Light.</span>


Not from outside.

<span class="glow">From within.</span>


Points emerge.

Sharp,
bright,
unstable.


They multiply.

They connect.


Lines become spirals.

Spirals expand,
layer upon layer,
turning,
folding,
endless.


You open your eyes.

But it does not stop.


The walls are no longer still.


Figures move.

Deer run across the stone,
their bodies stretched in motion.

Lines repeat,
echo,
transform.


<span class="glow">The cave is no longer a place.</span>

<span class="glow-strong glow-breath">It is a field of vision.</span>


Everything pulses.

Everything breathes.

Everything is connected.


You are not observing.


<span class="glow-strong glow-breath">You are inside the image.</span>


A distant understanding surfaces:


These forms are not invented.

<span class="glow">They are seen.</span>


Patterns that appear
when the mind crosses its own threshold.

Spirals,
grids,
points of light —
shared across places,
across time,
across bodies.


<span class="glow-breath">The painters saw them too.</span>


The vision intensifies.


Too much.


Too bright.


Too close.


—


Then


slowly


it recedes.


The spirals dissolve.

The figures slow.

The movement fades.


Darkness returns.


<span class="whisper">Silence.</span>


You are still here.


The <span style="color:#fff; text-shadow: 0 0 8px #ffcc66;">Sanctuary</span>.


The walls are still.

But something has changed.


You look down.

A mark on the surface.

A handprint.


<span class="glow-strong glow-breath">Yours.</span>

</div>

[[Continue]]

</div>


:: Go to the red hall {"position":"700,475","size":"100,100"}
You move deeper into the cave.

The darkness thickens.

<span class="glow-strong glow-breath">A faint red glow begins to emerge ahead of you —
not light, exactly,
but something suspended in the air.
</span>
You step forward.

The corridor opens.

The <span style="color:#ff4d4d; text-shadow: 0 0 6px #ff0000;">Red Hall</span>.


The walls are covered.

<span class="glow-strong glow-breath">Figures appear in the dim light:
two female bodies,
a hunter,
deer in motion.
</span>
They are not still.

The lines tremble slightly,
as if the pigment were not yet dry.


Water covers parts of the ground.
The surface reflects the walls —
doubling the images,
blurring what is real and what is not.


The silence is almost complete.

Only drops of water,
and your own breath —
louder than it should be.

Somewhere deeper inside,
a slow rhythm continues.

Closer now.


A voice, distant but calm:

<span class="glow-strong glow-breath">"This is the</span> <span style="color:#ff4d4d; text-shadow: 0 0 6px #ff0000;">Red Hall</span>.
<span class="glow-strong glow-breath">One of the central spaces of the cave.</span>

<span class="glow-strong glow-breath">The figures you see are among the oldest known
prehistoric paintings in this region.

The deer appear again and again.
They are not only animals,
but signs of movement,
of passage,
of transformation."</span>

<span class="glow-strong glow-breath">You feel you are not meant to simply observe.</span>


[[Approach the paintings]]
<video class="video-bg" autoplay loop muted playsinline>
  <source src="https://ChenQingHa.github.io/grotta-vr-media/鹿3.mp4" type="video/mp4">
</video>


