:: I will try drawing after the journey {"position":"375,1875","size":"100,100"}
<div class="map2">
<p class="whisper">The cave fades.</p>
<div class="poetic">
<span class="whisper">Not suddenly.</span>

<span class="whisper">Gradually.</span>


The walls dissolve.

The ceiling disappears.


<span class="glow">You are no longer inside.</span>


A space remains.

Undefined.

Without distance.


Then —


points of light.


One.

Then another.

Then many.


They arrange themselves.


<span class="glow-breath">A map.</span>


<span class="whisper">Not drawn.</span>

<span class="glow">Revealed.</span>


Each light marks a place.


You look.


A spiral.

Elsewhere.


A zigzag.

Again.


Dots.

Concentric lines.


Different lands.

Different times.


<span class="glow-strong glow-breath">The same forms.</span>


They did not meet.

They did not speak.


And yet —


<span class="glow">they saw the same things.</span>


Fifteen thousand years ago,
across continents,
human beings drew these patterns.


<span class="whisper">Not as symbols.</span>

<span class="glow">But as perception.</span>


What you saw
was not theirs alone.


<span class="glow-strong glow-breath">It belongs to the structure
of seeing itself.</span>


—


The map fades.


Your drawing appears.


Then others.


Layered.

Different hands.

Different places.


<span class="glow">The same attempt.</span>


To give form
to something that cannot be fully seen.


The space remains quiet.


The sound of wind returns.

The distant sea.


<span class="glow-breath">You are here again.</span>

</div>

[[Remove the headset]]

</div>


