:: Meet the devotee {"position":"25,675","size":"100,100"}
<div class="symbol3">
<p class="whisper">The spirals fade.

The space opens.</p>
<div class="poetic">
<span class="glow">You move forward.</span>

<span class="whisper">A threshold.</span>

<span class="whisper">A place before something greater.</span>


<span class="glow-breath">You are no longer alone.</span>


A figure emerges from the darkness.


<span class="whisper">Not suddenly —</span>

but as if they had always been there,
waiting to be seen.


Their body is simple,

almost drawn rather than formed.


Lines instead of flesh.

Shapes instead of features.


And yet —


<span class="glow">undeniably human.</span>


They approach you.


<span class="whisper">Hesitation in every step.</span>

</div>

<div class="intruder-voice">
"My daughter is ill.

I have come to ask...

what should I offer?"
</div>

<div class="poetic">

They look at you
as if you already know the answer.


<span class="glow">You feel the weight of your role.</span>


<span class="whisper">This is not a question of truth.</span>


<span class="glow-strong glow-breath">But of choice.</span>


What will you advise?

</div>


[[Offer the marked clay — patterns pressed into the surface->Pintaderas]]

[[Offer the shaped vessel — a body transformed into form->Ceramic Offering]]

[[Offer the black stone — sharp, rare, carried from afar->Obsidian Offering]]

</div>


